    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>DEFAULT BY CHINESE TRUST</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>China's Hainan International Trust and Investment Co defaults on bond issue for 14 billion Japanese yen, or about $130 million, after 14-day grace period lapses on missed payment (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>China's Hainan International Trust and Investment Company has defaulted on a bond issue for 14 billion Japanese yen, or about $130 million, after a 14-day grace period lapsed on a missed payment. The default is the latest of a string of financial scandals to rock Hainan Island, China's southernmost province and the country's fifth special economic zone. Japanese government officials are expected to raise the issue of China's investment environment with Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji when he visits Tokyo. It is unclear whether Japanese holders of the bonds will take legal action against the Hainan trust.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith</p>
      </block>
